---
description: Keep TypeScript types and interfaces in separate files
alwaysApply: true
---

# Type Separation Policy

- Always move shared TypeScript `type` and `interface` declarations to `src/types/`.
- Keep declarations split by kind:
  - `src/types/interfaces/` for interfaces
  - `src/types/enums/` for enum-like unions
  - `src/types/types/` for composite aliases
- One model declaration per file. File name must match the model purpose (for example `project.ts`, `next-action.ts`).
- Do not define reusable domain types inside components, hooks, or feature screens.
- Use barrel exports (`index.ts`) for convenient imports.

## Exceptions

- Local component props can stay in the same file only if used in exactly one component.
- If props are reused across files, move them to `src/types/interfaces/ui/`.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ Bad: shared domain interface inside a component file
interface Project {
  id: string
  title: string
}
```

```typescript
// ✅ Good: project model lives in src/types/interfaces/project.ts
export interface Project {
  id: string
  title: string
}
```
